article.description:
Noelle Quinn scored a season-high 25 points 
and Nikki Blue tied her season best with 24 points to lead UCLA to 
a 90-80 upset over Stanford (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) on Friday night.
article.headline: Quinn, Blue fuel UCLA upset over Stanford
article.linkText: Quinn, Blue fuel UCLA upset over Stanford
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) --Noelle Quinn scored a season-high 25 points 
and Nikki Blue tied her season best with 24 points to lead UCLA to 
a 90-80 upset over Stanford (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) on Friday night.

Lisa Willis added 16 points for the Bruins (11-8, 6-4 Pac-10), 
who broke a 14-game losing streak to Stanford dating back to 2000.

Brooke Smith had career highs of 26 points and 17 rebounds for 
the Cardinal (13-5, 8-2 Pac-10), whose seven-game winning streak 
ended.

Stanford's Candice Wiggins, the nation's fourth-leading scorer 
at 21.2 points, had 21 points in the second half to finish with 26.

Quinn scored 14 points and Blue had 11 points in the first 15 
minutes, as UCLA built a 38-23 lead with 4:41 left in the first 
half.

Krista Rappahahn made a 3-point basket to narrow the Cardinal's 
deficit to 81-72 with 2:36 to play. The Bruins, however, made seven 
of eight free throws in a 47-second span to expand their lead to 
88-75 with 1:14 remaining.
